        <h2 style="text-align:center;font-size: 22px;color:cyan;font-family">Onion Pakora</h2>

        <img style="padding-left:300px;" src="https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcSTc-f6Np-JPYFMqj8gBXLOryHlWk00YN76Qw&usqp=CAU" alt="Onion Pakora">
        <div id="en">
            <h3>Ingredients:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>4 large onions, thinly sliced</li>
                <li>2 cups gram flour (besan)</li>
                <li>1 teaspoon ginger garlic paste</li>
                <li>1 teaspoon red chili powder (adjust to taste)</li>
                <li>1/2 coriander powder</li>
                <li>1 teaspoon garam masala</li>
                <li>A pinch of Turmeric powder</li>
                <li>Salt to taste</li>
                <li>Oil for deep frying</li>
                <li>Water</li>
            </ul>
            <h3>Process:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <strong>Prepare the Batter:</strong><br />In a mixing bowl,gram flour (besan), ginger garlic paste, red chili powder, coriander powder, garam masala, turmeric powder.<br />
                    Mix the ingredients together.Add water and mix until you get a thick consistent batter that evenly coats the onions.
                </li>
                <li><strong>Add Onions:</strong><br />Add the thinly sliced onions to the bowl. Mix them until they are coated evenly.</li>
                <li><strong>Heat Oil:</strong><br />Heat oil in a deep frying pan or kadai over medium-high heat. To check if the oil is hot enough, drop a small amount of the batter into the oil; if it sizzles and rises to the surface, the oil is ready.</li>
                <li><strong>Fry the Pakoras:</strong><br />Carefully drop small portions of the onion mixture into the hot oil using a spoon or your hand.</li>
                <li><strong>Fry Until Golden Brown:</strong><br />Fry the pakoras until they turn golden brown and crispy. Be sure to flip them occasionally for even cooking. This should take about 4-5 minutes.</li>
                <li><strong>Drain:</strong><br />Using a slotted spoon, remove the pakoras from the oil and place them on a plate lined with paper towels to drain excess oil.</li>
                <li><strong>Serve Hot:</strong><br />Serve the hot and crispy onion pakoras immediately. You can enjoy them with green chutney or tamarind chutney and a cup of tea.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enjoy your homemade onion pakora :)</p>
